<div class="mb-requirement-container">
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-14147">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> </span>
      <b>NOTE: </b> The official merit badge pamphlets are now free and
      downloadable
      <a
        href="https://filestore.scouting.org/filestore/Merit_Badge_ReqandRes/Pamphlets/Public%20Speaking.pdf"
        target="_blank"
        >HERE</a
      >
      or can be purchased at the
      <a href="https://www.scoutshop.org/" target="_blank ">Scout Shop.</a>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-2260">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 1. </span>
      Give a three- to five-minute introduction of yourself to an audience such
      as your troop, class at school, or some other group. <br /><i
        >Resources:</i
      >
      <a href="https://youtu.be/l0Nve1zPvNkZ" target="_blank"
        >How To Introduce Yourself In A Speech (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://youtu.be/e_swBD_-yR4" target="_blank"
        >Introduction Speech Example (video)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-2261">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 2. </span>
      Prepare a three- to five-minute talk on a topic of your choice that
      incorporates body language and visual aids. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
      <a href="https://youtube.com/shorts/xmMfr8RtWkY" target="_blank"
        >How Should I Pick My Speech Topic? (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://youtu.be/ZK3jSXYBNak" target="_blank"
        >4 Essential Body Language Tips From a World Champion Public Speaker
        (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://youtu.be/QZ9_4mcMpS0" target="_blank"
        >3 Minute Speech: How to Craft a Memorable Short Speech? (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://youtube.com/shorts/IEAmkl7VmHU" target="_blank"
        >5 Presentation Aids to Make Your Presentation Pop (video)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-2262">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 3. </span>
      Give an impromptu talk of at least two minutes, either as part of a group
      discussion or before your counselor. Use a subject selected by your
      counselor that is interesting to you but that is not known to you in
      advance and for which you do not have time to prepare. <br /><i
        >Resources:</i
      >
      <a href="https://youtube.com/shorts/cOObqPtUlNk" target="_blank"
        >What is Impromptu Speaking? (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://youtube.com/shorts/PcbigPvCi1Y" target="_blank"
        >Mastering Impromptu Speaking: An Opportunity! (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://youtube.com/shorts/L87VlHjbm_M" target="_blank"
        >Mastering Impromptu Speaking: Deep Breaths and Go Slow (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://youtube.com/shorts/nsGHoxuH-VU" target="_blank"
        >How Do I Improve my Impromptu Speeches? (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://youtu.be/Rw2TZv56qO4" target="_blank"
        >How to Pick a Captivating Speech Topic (video)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-2263">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 4. </span>
      Select a topic of interest to your audience. Collect and organize
      information about the topic and prepare an outline. Write an eight- to
      10-minute speech, practice it, then deliver it in a conversational way.
      <br /><i>Resources:</i>
      <a href="https://youtube.com/shorts/5G9FQ7Gkt1g" target="_blank"
        >How to Prepare a Speech (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://youtube.com/shorts/zNpPaeRXVIs" target="_blank"
        >The Easiest Way to Practice for a Speech or Presentation (video)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-2264">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 5. </span>
      Show you know parliamentary procedure by leading a discussion or meeting
      according to accepted rules of order; or by answering questions on the
      rules of order. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
      <a href="https://youtu.be/Kit39MysFL4" target="_blank"
        >Robert's Rules (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://youtu.be/gDfhNGMO_0gl" target="_blank"
        >Roberts Rules of Order Updated (video)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
